26/04/2006
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- UN special envoy for Kosovo status negotiations Martti Ahtisaari said on Tuesday (25 April) that talks directly addressing status would begin in July at the earliest. His comment came during a meeting in Budapest with Hungarian Foreign Minister Ferenc Somogyi. Ahtisaari said technical discussions regarding decentralisation, protection of minority rights and economic issues must be completed before any talks on status are held. 
In other news Tuesday, UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen welcomed the launch of reconstruction efforts for the Roma Mahala neighbourhood in Mitrovica. The project envisions the construction of apartment blocks and houses, which would allow displaced people to return. (Politika - 26/04/06; Tanjug - 25/04/06)
